%3B%20Alan%20Fyall%2C%20the%20Visit%20Orlando%20endowed%20chair%20of%20tourism%20marketing%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Central%20Florida's%20Rosen%20College%20of%20Hospitality%20Management%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20the%20same%20places%20as%20everybody%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-lines-overtourism-develop-private-islands-exclusive-beaches-caribbean-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710457382000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f37958857f90b71522c976%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-lines-overtourism-develop-private-islands-exclusive-beaches-caribbean-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cruise%20lines%20are%20increasingly%20embracing%20private%20islands%20and%20exclusive%20beaches%2C%20in%20part%20in%20response%20to%20overtourism%20and%20complaints%20about%20cruise%20ships.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcruise-lines-overtourism-develop-private-islands-exclusive-beaches-caribbean-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20Begins%20Voting%20As%20Ukraine%20Steps%20Up%20Border%20Attacks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERussia%20began%20voting%20on%20Friday%20in%20an%20election%20set%20to%20prolong%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20rule%20by%20six%20more%20years%2C%20as%20Kyiv%20branded%20the%20vote%20a%20%26quot%3Bfarce%26quot%3B%20and%20launched%20a%20barrage%20of%20deadly%20attacks%20on%20border%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20in%20Moscow%20warned%20against%20any%20protests%20during%20the%20March%2015-17%20presidential%20vote%2C%20after%20calls%20from%20the%20opposition%20for%20anti-Putin%20demonstrations%20on%20Sunday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%20says%20the%20vote%20will%20show%20that%20the%20country%20is%20fully%20behind%20his%20assault%20on%20Ukraine%20and%20polling%20stations%20have%20been%20set%20up%20in%20Russian-held%20territories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%20election%2C%20Kyiv%20ramped%20up%20its%20aerial%20bombardment%20of%20Russian%20regions%20just%20across%20their%20shared%20border.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20National%20Guard%20said%20it%20was%20fighting%20off%20attacks%20from%20pro-Ukrainian%20militias%20in%20Kursk%2C%20the%20latest%20in%20a%20string%20of%20border%20clashes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20convinced%3A%20you%20realize%20what%20a%20difficult%20period%20our%20country%20is%20going%20through%2C%20what%20complex%20challenges%20we%20are%20facing%20in%20almost%20all%20areas%2C%26quot%3B%20Putin%20said%20in%20an%20address%20to%20Russians%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20vote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20in%20order%20to%20continue%20to%20respond%20to%20them%20with%20dignity%20and%20successfully%20overcome%20difficulties%2C%20we%20need%20to%20continue%20to%20be%20united%20and%20self-confident.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolling%20stations%20opened%20in%20Russia's%20easternmost%20Kamchatka%20peninsula%20at%208%3A00%20am%20local%20time%20on%20Friday%20and%20are%20set%20to%20close%20at%208%3A00%20pm%20(1800%20GMT)%20on%20Sunday%20in%20Kaliningrad%20--%20a%20Russian%20exclave%20bordering%20Poland%20and%20Lithuania.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E-%20'Border%20clashes'%20-%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20Putin's%20major%20critics%20are%20dead%2C%20in%20prison%20or%20in%20exile%2C%20and%20authorities%20blocked%20the%20few%20genuine%20competitors%20who%20tried%20to%20stand%20in%20the%20contest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlexei%20Navalny%2C%20Putin's%20most%20high-profile%20opponent%20over%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20died%20in%20February%20in%20an%20Arctic%20prison%20colony.%20He%20was%20serving%2019%20years%20for%20%26quot%3Bextremism%26quot%3B%2C%20a%20sentence%20widely%20seen%20as%20retribution%20for%20his%20campaigning%20against%20the%20Kremlin%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoscow%20prosecutors%20warned%20against%20protests%20during%20the%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20organization%20of%20and%20participation%20in%20these%20mass%20events%20are%20punishable%20by%20virtue%20of%20the%20legislation%20in%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20posted%20on%20Telegram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENavalny's%20widow%2C%20Yulia%20Navalnaya%2C%20has%20called%20for%20rallies%20outside%20polling%20stations%20on%20Sunday%2C%20the%20final%20day%20of%20voting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKyiv%20has%20this%20week%20launched%20some%20of%20its%20most%20significant%20aerial%20attacks%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20two-year%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20governor%20of%20Russia's%20Belgorod%20region%2C%20Vyacheslav%20Gladkov%2C%20said%20that%20at%20least%20three%20separate%20waves%20of%20aerial%20attacks%20had%20killed%20two%20people%2C%20wounding%20several%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20accused%20Ukraine%20of%20trying%20to%20%26quot%3Bsow%20panic%2C%20distrust%2C%20anger%2C%20and%20resentment%2C%20in%20order%20to%20break%20the%20unit%20of%20our%20society%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPro-Ukrainian%20paramilitaries%20also%20claimed%20to%20be%20escalating%20attacks%20and%20incursions%20in%20Russian%20border%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20joint%20statement%2C%20three%20pro-Kyiv%20volunteer%20groups%20--%20claiming%20to%20consist%20of%20anti-Kremlin%20Russians%20who%20have%20taken%20up%20arms%20--%20called%20on%20authorities%20to%20evacuate%20civilians%20from%20the%20regions%20of%20Belgorod%20and%20Kursk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCivilians%20should%20not%20suffer%20from%20the%20war%20and%20any%20casualties%20in%20the%20process%20of%20fighting%20will%20be%20on%20the%20conscience%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20regions'%20governors%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20denied%20militias'%20claims%20to%20have%20gained%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Guard%20said%20its%20units%20had%20beaten%20back%20one%20such%20attack%20near%20the%20village%20of%20Tyotkino%20in%20Kursk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20defense%20ministry%20said%20it%20had%20fended%20off%20another%20by%20Ukrainian%20forces%20trying%20to%20enter%20Belgorod%20via%20the%20village%20of%20Spodariushino%2C%20without%20saying%20when%20the%20clash%20had%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Not%20to%20stray'%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElection%20victory%20will%20allow%20Putin%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20Kremlin%20until%20at%20least%202030%2C%20a%20longer%20spell%20in%20power%20than%20any%20Russian%20leader%20since%20Catherine%20the%20Great%20in%20the%2018th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20called%20on%20Russians%20to%20use%20the%20vote%20to%20show%20their%20unity%20behind%20his%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20already%20shown%20that%20we%20can%20be%20together%2C%20defending%20the%20freedom%2C%20sovereignty%2C%20and%20security%20of%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20video%20message%2C%20flanked%20by%20flags%20of%20the%20Russian%20tricolor%20and%20the%20president's%20state%20insignia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%20it%20is%20critically%20important%20not%20to%20stray%20from%20this%20path%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarly%20voting%20was%20already%20underway%20in%20occupied%20territories%20of%20Ukraine.%20The%20vote%20will%20also%20take%20place%20in%20Crimea%2C%20the%20peninsula%20annexed%20by%20Moscow%20in%202014%20--%20a%20move%20that%20most%20of%20the%20international%20community%20refuses%20to%20recognize.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20State%20Department%20spokesman%20Matthew%20Miller%20condemned%20the%20voting%20in%20Russian-held%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20United%20States%20does%20not%20and%20will%20never%20recognize%20the%20legitimacy%20or%20outcome%20of%20these%20sham%20electi