5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJealousy%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20common%20human%20emotions.%20But%20it's%20complicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20genuinely%20jealous%20of%20someone%2C%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20admit%20to%20it%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20somehow%20shameful%2C%20or%20even%20taboo.%20Being%20on%20the%20receiving%20end%20of%20jealousy%20is%20also%20confusing%2C%20having%20great%20news%20to%20share%20but%20suspecting%20your%20bestie%20isn't%20all%20that%20enthused%20about%20your%20joy.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20outwardly%20asking%20them%20about%20it%20probably%20won't%20get%20you%20anywhere%20(and%20can%20offend%20them%20if%20you're%20totally%20off).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20you%20decide%20it's%20jealousy%2C%20clinical%20psychologist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.miriamkirmayer.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDr.%20Miriam%20Kirmayer%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20you%20should%20first%20ask%20yourself%3A%20am%20I%20the%20problem%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20definitely%20encourage%20people%20to%20look%20at%20both%20sides%20of%20it%2C%20not%20only%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20is%20this%20telling%20you%20about%20your%20friend%2C%20but%20what%20is%20this%20telling%20you%20about%20yourself%3F%26quot%3B%20Kirmayer%2C%20a%20keynote%20speaker%20on%20social%20connection%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20often%20are%20you%20sharing%20exciting%20life%20updates%3F%20How%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-sided-friendship-signs-to-look-out-for-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emuch%20do%20you%20support%20them%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it's%20their%20turn%20to%20shine%3F%20If%20you%20rattle%20off%20your%20promotion%20and%20upcoming%20Paris%20trip%20when%20your%20friend%20just%20got%20laid%20off%20and%20is%20scared%20of%20making%20rent%2C%20that%20feeling%20of%20%26quot%3Bjealousy%26quot%3B%20might%20be%20more%20extreme%20(justified)%20annoyance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you're%20sure%20you%20aren't%20the%20humblebrag%20express%2C%20Kirmayer%20shared%20some%20signs%20a%20friend%20might%20actually%20be%20jealous%20of%20you.%20Depending%20on%20how%20they%20express%20it%2C%20it%20can%20be%20a%20way%20to%20grow%20closer%20%E2%80%94%20or%20know%20that%20you've%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-you-outgrowing-done-friendship-move-past-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoutgrown%20this%20friendship%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20They're%20more%20interested%20in%20the%20hard%20parts%20of%20your%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20friend%20who's%20only%20interested%20in%20talking%20about%20the%20pain%20points%20in%20life%20and%20not%20something%20that's%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20hopeful%20or%20optimistic%2C%20that%20can%20potentially%20be%20a%20sign%20that%20they%20themselves%20are%20wrestling%20with%20feelings%20of%20envy%20or%20competition%2C%26quot%3B%20Kirmayer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20do%20have%20good%20news%20to%20share%2C%20Kirmayer%20said%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbird-test-bids-deeper-relationships-friendships-gottman-institute-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emight%20not%20ask%20many%20follow-up%20questions%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20acknowledge%20it%20too%20much.%20They%20might%20be%20wonderful%20confidants%20when%20you're%20going%20through%20a%20breakup%2C%20but%20not%20have%20much%20to%20say%20when%20you%20start%20dating%20someone%20new.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20They%20compare%20your%20successes%20to%20other%20people's%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20more%20classic%20(but%20sometimes%20nuanced)%20sign%20of%20jealousy%20is%20a%20friend%20minimizing%20or%20even%20invalidating%20your%20accomplishments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Kirmayer%2C%20it%20can%20be%20quite%20subtle%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20not%20like%20your%20friend%20is%20outwardly%20saying%20%26quot%3BWho%20cares%3F%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BDon't%20get%20too%20excited.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20it%20can%20%26quot%3Boften%20take%20the%20form%20of%20one-upmanship%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20If%20you%20just%20won%20an%20award%2C%20your%20friend%20might%20bring%20up%20their%20own%20from%20a%20year%20ago.%20Or%20if%20you%20just%20bought%20a%20studio%20apartment%2C%20they%20might%20bring%20up%20a%20friend%20of%20theirs%20who%20just%20closed%20on%20a%20three-bedroom%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20They%20copy%20you%20without%20giving%20credit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjealousy-in-friendship-jealous-of-a-friend-benefits-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJealousy%20can%20have%20some%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20some%20friends%20might%20use%20theirs%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-law-associate-quit-job-jealousy-career-life-goals-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eguiding%20light%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20finding%20what%20they%20want%20more%20out%20of%20their%20own%20life.%20Kirmayer%20said%20that%20this%20part%20can%20be%20healthy%20and%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20is%20if%20they%20start%20taking%20up%20the%20same%20hobbies%2C%20pursuing%20the%20same%20degree%2C%20or%20copying%20your%20fashion%20without%20telling%20you%20that%20they%20were%20positively%20influenced%20by%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAre%20they%20open%20about%20where%20their%20inspiration%20came%20from%3F%26quot%3B%20Kirmayer%20said.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%2C%20all%20we%20really%20want%20to%20hear%20is%20that%20that's%20where%20this%20idea%20came%20from.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20transparency%20is%20something%20Kirmayer%20said%20she's%20seen%20cause%20a%20lot%20of%20friendship%20issues%2C%20as%20one%20friend%20might%20feel%20like%20another's%20competition%20instead%20of%20their%20aspiration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20They%20put%20themselves%20down%20to%20build%20you%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJealousy%20among%20friends%20doesn't%20always%20look%20like%20them%20putting%20you%20down.%20Kirmayer%20said%20the%20other%20response%20can%20be%20their%20self-deprecation%20when%20you%20have%20something%20good%20happen%20to%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20you%20get%20engaged%2C%20they%20might%20make%20a%20joke%20about%20dying%20alone.%20Or%20if%20you%20throw%20a%20party%2C%20they%20might%20start%20talking%20about%20how%20they%20only%20have%20two%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Their%20%26quot%3Bcongrats%26quot%3B%20feels%20stiff%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20the%20vibes%20are%20just%20off.%20%26quot%3BYou%20get%20the%20sense%20that%20when%20they%20celebrate%2C%20it%20ends%20up%20being%20a%20little%20bit%20performative%20and%20forced%2C%26quot%3B%20Kirmayer%20said.%20They%20might%20say%20and%20do%20all%20the%20textbook%20supportive%20things%2C%20but%20you%20might%20still%20feel%20that%20they're%20jealous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20should%20end%20your%20friendship%2C%20though.%20Kirmayer%20said%20that%20jealousy%20can%20bring%20friends%20closer%20%E2%80%94%20if%20they%20can%20have%20honest%20conversations%20about%20it.%20If%20your%20friend%20opens%20up%20about%20their%20feelings%20(while%20still%20being%20excited%20for%20you)%2C%20you%20can%20also%20temporarily%20refrain%20from%20sharing%20updates%20about%20your%20new%20job%20while%20they're%20still%20looking%20for%20one%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubtle-signs-your-friend-is-jealous-of-you-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710452497000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f0c1ae6080194819ff3227%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubtle-signs-your-friend-is-jealous-of-you-20