ion%20Commission%20seeking%20modification%20of%20the%20operative%20portion%20of%20its%20March%2011%20order%20in%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20poll%20panel%20said%20the%20order%20had%20noted%20that%20copies%20of%20the%20documents%20submitted%20by%20it%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20sealed%20cover%20during%20the%20course%20of%20hearing%20be%20maintained%20at%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission.%20The%20EC%20said%20it%20did%20not%20keep%20any%20copy%20of%20the%20documents%20and%20added%20that%20they%20may%20be%20returned%20so%20that%20it%20can%20comply%20with%20the%20court%20directions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20separate%20petition%20filed%20by%20NGO%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20challenging%20the%20exclusion%20of%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20from%20a%20panel%20for%20the%20selection%20of%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20and%20election%20commissioners%20was%20also%20scheduled%20to%20come%20up%20for%20hearing%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20matter%20is%20not%20shown%20in%20Friday's%20list%20of%20business%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20headed%20by%20Justice%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20on%20March%2012%20had%20told%20advocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%2C%20representing%20the%20NGO%2C%20that%20the%20plea%20on%20the%20exclusion%20of%20CJI%20from%20the%20selection%20panel%20will%20be%20taken%20up%20for%20hearing%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case%2C%20the%20Supreme%20had%20on%20March%2011%20directed%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI)%20to%20disclose%20the%20details%20of%20the%20bonds%20to%20the%20EC%20by%20close%20of%20business%20hours%20on%20March%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20fresh%20application%2C%20the%20poll%20panel%20has%20said%20the%20Supreme%20court%20had%20observed%20in%20its%20March%2011%20order%20that%20%26quot%3Bcopies%20of%20the%20statements%20which%20were%20filed%20by%20the%20ECI%20before%20this%20court%20would%20be%20maintained%20in%20the%20office%20of%20the%20ECI%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20most%20respectfully%20submitted%20herein%20that%20in%20compliance%20of%20the%20orders%20passed%20by%20this%20court%20and%20in%20order%20to%20maintain%20the%20confidentiality%20of%20the%20aforesaid%20information%20%2Fdata%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20forwarded%20the%20documents%20received%20by%20it%20to%20this%20court%20in%20sealed%20covers%2Fboxes%2C%20without%20retaining%20any%20copies%20of%20the%20same%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20application%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThus%2C%20no%20copies%20of%20the%20documents%2Fstatements%20filed%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20before%20this%20court%20in%20the%20instant%20case%20were%20ever%20retained%20by%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20application%2C%20the%20EC%20has%20urged%20the%20Supreme%20that%20the%20portion%20of%20March%2011%20order%20may%20be%20rectified%20or%20modified%20and%20the%20documents%2C%20data%20or%20information%20submitted%20by%20it%20before%20the%20court%20in%20sealed%20covers%20may%20be%20returned%20to%20it%20to%20enable%20the%20poll%20panel%20to%20comply%20with%20the%20court's%20directions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20application%20said%20pursuant%20to%20the%20directions%20passed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20its%20April%2012%2C%202019%20and%20November%202%20last%20year%20orders%2C%20the%20EC%20had%20produced%20information%2Fdata%20so%20sought%2C%20both%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover%20(containing%20106%20sealed%20envelopes)%20and%20in%20sealed%20boxes%20(containing%20309%20and%20214%20sealed%20envelopes%20respectively).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2012%2C%202019%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20issued%20an%20interim%20order%20directing%20that%20the%20information%20of%20donations%20received%20and%20donations%20which%20will%20be%20received%20must%20be%20submitted%20by%20political%20parties%20to%20the%20EC%20in%20a%20sealed%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20five-judge%20Constitution%20bench%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D%20Y%20Chandrachud%20is%20scheduled%20to%20hear%20the%20EC's%20application%20on%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20March%2011%20order%2C%20the%20top%20court%20dismissed%20SBI's%20plea%20seeking%20an%20extension%20of%20time%20and%20ordered%20it%20to%20disclose%20the%20details%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20to%20the%20EC%20by%20close%20of%20business%20hours%20on%20March%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20had%20also%20directed%20the%20EC%20to%20publish%20the%20details%20shared%20by%20the%20bank%20on%20its%20official%20website%20by%205%20pm%20on%20March%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Election%20Commission%20put%20up%20on%20its%20website%20the%20data%20on%20electoral%20bonds%20on%20Thursday%2C%20a%20day%20before%20the%20deadline.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710441360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F4qgfvaco_supreme-court-new_625x300_11_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-to-hear-poll-bodys-application-in-electoral-bonds-case-tomorrow-5239967%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20scheduled%20to%20hear%20on%20Friday%20an%20application%20filed%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20seeking%20modification%20of%20the%20operative%20portion%20of%20its%20March%2011%20order%20in%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-to-hear-poll-bodys-application-in-electoral-bonds-case-tomorrow-5239967%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-to-hear-poll-bodys-application-in-electoral-bonds-case-tomorrow-5239967%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsupreme-court-to-hear-poll-bodys-application-in-electoral-bonds-case-tomorrow-5239967%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Meta%20sees%20big%20opportunity%20in%20gaming%20industry%3A%20MD%20Sandhya%20Devanathan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710440913000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-09%2F10%2Ffull%2F1694354767-2355.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fpeople%2Fmeta-sees-big-opportunity-in-gaming-industry-md-sandhya-devanathan-124031401084_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20a%20study%20by%20GWI%2C%20an%20audience%20research%20company%2090%20per%20cent%20of%20gamers%20who%20discover%20new%20games%20on%20social%20media%2C%20do%20so%20through%20Meta%20with%20Reels%20playing%20a%20leading%20role%20in%20discovery%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fpeople%2Fmeta-sees-big-opportunity-in-gaming-industry-md-sandhya-devanathan-124031401084_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fpeople%2Fmeta-sees-big-opportunity-in-gaming-industry-md-sandhya-devanathan-124031401084_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fpeople%2Fmeta-sees-big-opportunity-in-gaming-industry-md-sandhya-devanathan-124031401084_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Top%2010%20Recommendations%20Of%20Ex-President-Led%20Panel%20On%20Simultaneous%20Polls%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20government%20must%20develop%20a%20legally%20tenable%20mechanism%20to%20restore%20the%20cycle%20of%20simultaneous%20elections.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20first%20stage%2C%20elections%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20all%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%20can%20be%20held%20together.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20second%20step%2C%20the%20elections%20to%20municipalities%20and%20panchayats%20will%20be%20synchronised%20with%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies%20in%20such%20a%20way%20that%20elections%20to%20municipalities%20and%20panchayats%20are%20held%20within%20100%20days%20of%20the%20holding%20of%20parliamentary%20and%20assembly%20polls.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETo%20synchronise%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20assembly%20elections%2C%20the%20president%20shall%20notify%20the%20date%20of%20the%20first%20sitting%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20after%20a%20general%20election%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bappointed%20date%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20tenure%20of%20all%20state%20assemblies%20formed%20via%20polls%20after%20the%20%26quot%3Bappointed%20date%26quot%3B%20and%20before%20the%20expiry%20of%20the%20full%20term%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20will%20be%20only%20for%20the%20period%20ending%20up%20to%20the%20subsequent%20parliamentary%20polls.%20After%20this%20one-time%20transitory%20measure%2C%20all%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20assembly%20polls%20will%20be%20held%20simultaneously.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFresh%20elections%20could%20be%20held%20to%20constitute%20a%20new%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20hung%20House%20a%20no-confidence%20motion%2C%20or%20any%20such%20event.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhere%20fresh%20elections%20are%20held%20for%20the%20House%20of%20the%20People%20(Lok%20Sabha)%2C%20the%20tenure%20of%20the%20House%20will%20be%20%26quot%3Bonly%20for%20the%20unexpired%20(remaining)%20term%20of%20the%20immediately%20preceding%20full%20term%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhen%20fresh%20elections%20are%20held%20for%20state%20legislative%20assemblies%2C%20then%20such%20new%20assemblies%20--%20unless%20sooner%20dissolved%20--%20shall%20continue%20up%20to%20the%20end%20of%20the%20full%20term%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20single%20electoral%20roll%20and%20Elector's%20Photo%20Identity%20Card%20(EPIC)%20shall%20be%20prepared%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20in%20consultation%20with%20the%20State%20Election%20Commission%20and%20the%20same%20will%20substitute%20any%20other%20electoral%20roll%20prepared%20by%20ECI.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFor%20making%20logistical%20arrangements%20for%20the%20conduct%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%2C%20the%20ECI%20may%20draw%20up%20a%20plan%20and%20estimate%20in%20advance%20for%20the%20procurement%20of%20equipment%2C%20such%20as%20EVMs%20and%20VVPATs%2C%20deployment%20of%20polling%20personnel%20and%20security%20forces%20and%20make%20other%20necessary%20arrangements.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710440760000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fpe4hgdl4_one-nation-one-election-panel-ani_625x300_14_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftop-10-recommendations-of-ex-president-ram-nath-kovind-led-panel-on-simultaneous-polls-5240115%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20high-level%20panel%20led%20by%20former%20president%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%20submitted%20its%20report%20on%20'One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election'%20on%20Thursday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftop-10-recommendations-of-ex-president-ram-nath-kovind-led-panel-on-simultaneous-polls-5240115%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftop-10-recommendations-of-ex-president-ram-nath-kovind-led-panel-on-simultaneous-polls-5240115%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftop-10-recommendations-of-ex-president-ram-nath-kovind-led-panel-on-simultaneous-p