2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15173435%2FMumbai.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20ranks%20at%20134%20on%20the%20global%20Human%20Development%20Index%20(HDI)%2C%20according%20to%20United%20Nations%20Development%20Programme%E2%80%99s%20(UNDP%E2%80%99s)%20latest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhdr.undp.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fdocuments%2Fglobal-report-document%2Fhdr2023-24reporten.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20human%20development.%20The%20report%20also%20revealed%20that%20affluent%20countries%20are%20experiencing%20unprecedented%20levels%20of%20growth%2C%20while%20half%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20poorest%20nations%20have%20failed%20to%20regain%20their%20pre-pandemic%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%202023%2F24%20Human%20Development%20Report%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98Breaking%20the%20Gridlock%3A%20Reimagining%20cooperation%20in%20a%20polarized%20world%2C%E2%80%99%20while%20HDI%20is%20projected%20to%20reach%20record%20highs%20in%202023%20after%20declines%20in%202020%20and%202021%2C%20there%20is%20a%20stark%20contrast%20in%20development%20levels%20between%20rich%20and%20poor%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20points%20out%20that%20global%20inequalities%20have%20been%20compounded%20by%20substantial%20economic%20concentration%20%E2%80%93%20almost%2040%25%20of%20global%20trade%20in%20goods%20is%20concentrated%20in%20three%20or%20fewer%20countries.%20In%202021%2C%20the%20market%20capitalisation%20of%20each%20of%20the%20three%20largest%20tech%20companies%20in%20the%20world%20surpassed%20the%20Gross%20Domestic%20Product%20(GDP)%20of%20more%20than%2090%25%20of%20countries%20that%20year%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20widening%20human%20development%20gap%20revealed%20by%20the%20report%20shows%20that%20the%20two-decade%20trend%20of%20steadily%20reducing%20inequalities%20between%20wealthy%20and%20poor%20nations%20is%20now%20in%20reverse.%20Despite%20our%20deeply%20interconnected%20global%20societies%2C%20we%20are%20falling%20short.%20We%20must%20leverage%20our%20interdependence%20as%20well%20as%20our%20capacities%20to%20address%20our%20shared%20and%20existential%20challenges%20and%20ensure%20people%E2%80%99s%20aspirations%20are%20met%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Achim%20Steiner%2C%20head%20of%20the%20UN%20Development%20Programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20gridlock%20carries%20a%20significant%20human%20toll.%20The%20failure%20of%20collective%20action%20to%20advance%20action%20on%20climate%20change%2C%20digitalisation%20or%20poverty%20and%20inequality%20not%20only%20hinders%20human%20development%20but%20also%20worsens%20polarisation%20and%20further%20erodes%20trust%20in%20people%20and%20institutions%20worldwide%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20rank%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECategorised%20as%20%E2%80%98Very%20High%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98High%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98Medium%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Low%20Human%20Development%E2%80%99%2C%20China%20and%20Sri%20Lanka%2C%20ranked%20at%2075%20and%2078%2C%20respectively%2C%20in%20the%20High%20Human%20Development%20category%20compared%20to%20India%2C%20which%20stands%20at%20134.%20India%20also%20ranks%20below%20Bhutan%20(125)%20and%20Bangladesh%20(129)%2C%20despite%20all%20three%20being%20categorised%20under%20%E2%80%98Medium%20Human%20Development%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Democracy%20paradox%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20while%20nine%20in%2010%20people%20worldwide%20endorse%20democracy%2C%20over%20half%20of%20the%20respondents%20expressed%20support%20for%20leaders%20that%20may%20undermine%20it%20by%20bypassing%20fundamental%20rules%20of%20the%20democratic%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20this%20paradox%2C%20half%20of%20the%20people%20surveyed%20reported%20having%20no%20or%20limited%20control%20over%20their%20lives%2C%20and%20over%20two-thirds%20believed%20that%20they%20have%20little%20influence%20on%20their%20government%E2%80%99s%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolitical%20polarisation%20in%20countries%20is%20also%20responsible%20for%20protectionist%20or%20%3Cspan%3Einward-turning%20policy%20approaches%20which%20is%20%E2%80%9Cstarkly%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20global%20cooperation%20needed%20to%20address%20urgent%20issues%20like%20the%20decarbonisation%20of%20our%20economies%2C%20misuse%20of%20digital%20technologies%2C%20and%20conflict%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20says%20while%20emphasising%20on%20the%20need%20for%20united%20action%20to%20tackle%20global%20issues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20world%20marked%20by%20increasing%20polarisation%20and%20division%2C%20neglecting%20to%20invest%20in%20each%20other%20poses%20a%20serious%20threat%20to%20our%20wellbeing%20and%20security.%20Protectionist%20approaches%20cannot%20address%20the%20complex%2C%20interconnected%20challenges%20we%20face%2C%20including%20pandemic%20prevention%2C%20climate%20change%2C%20and%20digital%20regulation%2C%E2%80%9D%20Steiner%20added.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COur%20problems%20are%20intertwined%2C%20requiring%20equally%20interconnected%20solutions.%20By%20adopting%20an%20opportunity-driven%20agenda%20that%20emphasises%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20energy%20transition%20and%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20for%20human%20development%2C%20we%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20break%20through%20the%20current%20deadlock%20and%20reignite%20a%20commitment%20to%20a%20shared%20future%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710423907000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15173435%2FMumbai.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fhuman-development-index-india-ranks-134th-falls-behind-bangladesh-sri-lanka-bhutan-and-china%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%2