s%20numbers%20showing%20that%2012%2C193%20children%20had%20been%20killed%20in%20conflicts%20worldwide%20between%202019%20and%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20compared%20that%20to%20reports%20from%20the%20health%20ministry%20in%20Hamas-run%20Gaza%20indicating%20that%20more%20than%2012%2C300%20children%20died%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20territory%20between%20last%20October%20and%20the%20end%20of%20February%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710418530000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F14163650%2Fimage-1956.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fun-says-more-children-killed-in-gaza-than-four-years-of-global-conflict-combined%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'This%20war%20is%20a%20war%20on%20children.%20It%20is%20a%20war%20on%20their%20childhood%20and%20their%20future%2C'%20said%20Philippe%20Lazzarini%2C%20head%20of%20the%20UN%20agency%20for%20Palestinian%20refugees.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fun-says-more-children-killed-in-gaza-than-four-years-of-global-conflict-combined%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Taken%20India%20For%20A%20Ride'%3A%20Why%20Supreme%20Court's%20Order%20Against%20Patanjali%20Is%20A%20Significant%20Step%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F09164656%2Framdev.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2027%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftaken-for-a-ride-sc-issues-contempt-notice-to-patanjali-ayurved-its-md-over-misleading-ads%5C%22%3E%20issued%20a%20contempt%20notice%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Patanjali%20Ayurved%2C%20the%20company%20founded%20by%20yoga%20guru%20Ramdev%2C%20and%20its%20managing%20director%20Acharya%20Balakrishna.%20This%20notice%20was%20in%20response%20to%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20continued%20dissemination%20of%20misleading%20advertisements%20claiming%20to%20offer%20permanent%20cures%20for%20various%20diseases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20bench%20consisting%20of%20Justices%20Hima%20Kohli%20and%20Ahsanuddin%20Amanullah%2C%20strongly%20criticised%20Patanjali%20Ayurved%20for%20its%20misleading%20advertising%20practices%20and%20temporarily%20banned%20the%20company%20from%20marketing%20its%20products%20until%20further%20notice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20an%20assurance%20given%20to%20the%20court%20in%20November%202023%2C%20wherein%20the%20company%20promised%20not%20to%20release%20any%20statements%20that%20made%20unsubstantiated%20claims%20about%20medicinal%20efficacy%20or%20criticise%20any%20system%20of%20medicine%2C%20Patanjali%20Ayurved%20persisted%20in%20its%20misleading%20advertisements.%20The%20bench%20remarked%20that%20the%20entire%20nation%20had%20been%20deceived%20by%20these%20actions.%20Furthermore%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20also%20admonished%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20failing%20to%20take%20any%20action%20against%20these%20advertisements%20despite%20being%20aware%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20case%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20goes%20back%20to%20the%20year%202022.%20In%20August%202022%2C%20the%20Indian%20Medical%20Association%20(IMA)%20took%20legal%20action%20in%20response%20to%20a%20Patanjali%20advertisement%20titled%20%E2%80%9CMisconceptions%20spread%20by%20allopathy%3A%20Save%20yourself%20and%20the%20country%20from%20the%20misconceptions%20spread%20by%20pharma%20and%20medical%20industry.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petition%20raised%20two%20main%20concerns%3A%20firstly%2C%20it%20accused%20Patanjali%20of%20consistently%20disseminating%20misinformation%20to%20denigrate%20allopathy%2C%20which%20it%20deemed%20as%20a%20deliberate%20and%20ongoing%20campaign.%20Secondly%2C%20it%20alleged%20that%20Patanjali%20was%20making%20exaggerated%20claims%20about%20the%20efficacy%20of%20its%20drugs%2C%20purportedly%20based%20on%20scientific%20evidence%2C%20which%20contradicted%20regulations%20banning%20such%20advertisements%20in%20the%20country.%20According%20to%20the%20IMA%2C%20these%20statements%20violated%20both%20the%20Drugs%20and%20Other%20Magical%20Remedies%20Act%2C%201954%20(DOMA)%20and%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%2C%202019%20(CPA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20Patanjali%E2%80%99s%20Divya%20Amla%20Juice%2C%20recommended%20for%20individuals%20with%20diabetes%2C%20and%20Shivlingi%20Beej%20were%20deemed%20of%20%E2%80%98substandard%20quality%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20Ayurveda%20and%20Unani%20Office%20in%20Haridwar%2C%20as%20revealed%20in%20a%20Right%20to%20Information%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202022%2C%20Nepal%E2%80%99s%20drug%20regulator%20blacklisted%20Patanjali%E2%80%99s%20Divya%20Pharmacy%20for%20failing%20to%20adhere%20to%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20drug%20manufacturing%20standards.%20Additional%20reports%20have%20also%20raised%20concerns%20regarding%20Patanjali%E2%80%99s%20questionable%20quality%20control%20measures%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20robust%20clinical%20trial%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2021%2C%202023%2C%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20comprising%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-patanjali-baba-ramdev-misleading-advertisements-indian-medical-association-242694%5C%22%3E%20Justices%20Ahsanuddin%20Amanullah%20and%20Prashant%20Kumar%20Mishra%3C%2Fa%3E%20cautioned%20Patanjali%20against%20advertising%20permanent%20cures%20and%20threatened%20to%20levy%20a%20penalty%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20for%20each%20product%20making%20such%20claims.%20The%20court%20declined%20to%20engage%20in%20the%20%E2%80%9CAllopathy%20v.%20Ayurveda%E2%80%9D%20discourse%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20assurances%20to%20the%20court%2C%20pledging%20no%20violation%20of%20laws%2C%20especially%20regarding%20product%20advertising%2C%20and%20refraining%20from%20making%20disparaging%20remarks%20about%20any%20medical%20system%2C%20Patanjali%20failed%20to%20uphold%20these%20commitments.%20Soon%20after%20the%20hearing%2C%20Baba%20Ramdev%20praised%20Patanjali%20products%20at%20a%20press%20conference%2C%20followed%20by%20advertisements%20appearing%20in%20mainstream%20media%20in%20December%202023%20and%20January%202024.%20These%20actions%20contravened%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20promise%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20strong%20dose%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20to%20enforce%20a%20ban%20on%20Patanjali%E2%80%99s%20advertisements%20marks%20a%20pivotal%20step%20in%20addressing%20the%20ongoing%20problem%20of%20misleading%20medical%20advertising.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20society%20where%20many%20individuals%20lack%20sufficient%20knowledge%20of%20medical%20science%20and%20tend%20to%20place%20unwarranted%20faith%20in%20unverified%20herbal%20remedies%2C%20such%20advertising%20practices%20present%20a%20considerable%20risk.%20They%20propagate%20misinformation%20and%20may%20endorse%20products%20that%20could%20potentially%20pose%20harm%20to%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20efforts%20such%20as%20the%20collaboration%20between%20the%20Ministry%20of%20AYUSH%20and%20the%20Advertising%20Standards%20Council%20of%20India%20to%20tackle%20misleading%20advertisements%2C%20Patanjali%20continued%20to%20spread%20misinformation%20unchecked.%20The%20court%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20signifies%20a%20crucial%20move%20towards%20protecting%20public%20health%20and%20ensuring%20accountability%20in%20the%20marketing%20of%20healthcare%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20persisted%20even%20when%20it%20was%20warned%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20as%20early%20as%20November%202023%20to%20cease%20disseminating%20these%20assertions%20or%20risk%20substantial%20fines%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%201%20crore%20for%20each%20product%20featuring%20false%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20court%20reprimanded%20the%20government%20for%20its%20apparent%20negligence%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20turning%20a%20blind%20eye%20while%20the%20nation%20was%20deceived.%20The%20government%20could%20have%20legally%20compelled%20Patanjali%20to%20retract%20its%20advertisements%2C%20which%20flagrantly%20contravened%20Section%204%20of%20the%20Drugs%20and%20Other%20Magical%20Remedies%20Act%20(DOMA)%2C%201954%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%2C%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20current%20legal%20framework%2C%20dissemination%20of%20misleading%20advertisements%20carries%20penalties.%20A%20first%20offence%20under%20the%20Drug%20and%20Magic%20Remedies%20(Objectionable%20Advertisements)%20Act%20(DOMA)%20could%20lead%20to%20imprisonment%20for%20six%20months%20and%2For%20a%20fine.%20For%20subsequent%20offences%2C%20the%20punishment%20may%20extend%20to%20one%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20the%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%20imposes%20stricter%20consequences%2C%20with%20a%20potential%20imprisonment%20term%20of%20up%20to%20two%20years%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20around%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20for%20violations.%20Repeat%20offences%20escalate%20to%20a%20five-year%20imprisonment%20term%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20approximately%20Rs%2050%20lakh.%20The%20government%20has%20committed%20to%20investigating%20allegations%20and%20proposing%20appropriate%20actions.%20Strengthening%20advertising%20regulations%20for%20both%20Ayurvedic%20and%20over-the-counter%20(OTC)%20allopathic%20drugs%20should%20be%20a%20priority%20in%20this%20regard.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20operate%20in%20grey%20areas.%20For%20instance%2C%20DOMA%20does%20not%20recognise%20a%20list%20of%20drugs%20for%20which%20any%20advertisement%20is%20prohibited.%20But%20that%20still%20leaves%20the%20field%20dangerously%20open%20for%20all%20manner%20of%20products%2C%20including%20some%20vaccines.%20As%20for%20advertisements%20for%20ayurvedic%20products%2C%20these%20are%20more%20common%20than%20their%20allopathic%20counterparts%20because%20they%20do%20not%20require%20pre-approval%20or%20any%20stipulation%20of%20minimum%20information%20for%20the%20consumer.%20Indians%20who%20struggle%20with%20medical%20expenses%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20growing%20promotion%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Cindigenous%E2%80%9D%20medical%20system%20supposedly%20offering%20cheaper%20remedies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPatanjali%E2%80%99s%20prosperity%20and%20its%20ability%20to%20evade%20legal%20scrutiny%20highlight%20a%20troubling%20issue%3A%20the%20lack%20of%20accessible%20and%20affordable%20healthcare.%20The%20underprivileged%20find%20themselves%20trapped%2C%20facing%20a%20choice%20between%20enduring%20delayed%20treatment%20from%20conventional%20medicine%20or%20falling%20victim%20to%20misleading%20and%20exploitative%20advertising%2C%20exacerbating%20their%20plight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeceptive%20advertisements%20not%20only%20breach%20legal%20standards%20but%20also%20endanger%20public%20health%20by%20disseminating%20misinformation%20about%20evidence-based%20treatments%20and%20targeting%20vulnerable%20individuals.%20Patanjali%E2%80%99s%20misleading%20advertising%20practices%20are%20acknowledged%20as%20a%20critical%20public%20health%20concern%20demanding%20urgent%20intervention.%20The%20recent%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20represents%20a%20positive%20initial%20move%20towards%20overhauling%20the%20regulations%20overseeing%20this%20medical%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EShivanand%20Pandit%20is%20an%20autonomous%20finance%20and%20tax%20adviser.%20He%20has%2028%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20finance%2C%20accounting%2C%20taxation%20laws%2C%20cost%20management%2C%20wealth%20management%2C%20audit%2C%20corporate%20and%20banking%20laws.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710414008000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F08%2F09164656%2Framdev.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftaken-india-for-a-ride-why-supreme-courts-order-against-patanjali-is-a-significant-step%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Indians%20who%20struggle%20with%20medical%20expenses%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20growing%20promotion%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Cindigenous%E2%80%9D%20medical%20system%20supposedly%20offering%20cheaper%20remedies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftaken-india-for-a-ride-why-supreme-courts-order-against-patanjali-is-a-significant-step%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%224000%2B%20People%20Are%20Getting%20Life-Saving%20Dialysis%20Through%20This%20Amazing%20Initiative%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20sponsored%20by%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrakala%20Devi%2C%20an%20ASHA%20worker%20from%20Uttarakhand%E2%80%99s%20Chamoli%20district%2C%20started%20experiencing%20severe%20body%20pain%2C%20fever%2C%20chills%2C%20nausea%2C%20and%20difficulty%20walking%20in%20late%202021.%20During%20the%20course%20of%20her%20work%20in%20her%20district%2C%20these%20symptoms%20caused%20her%20considerable%20discomfort%20and%20made%20it%20difficult%20for%20her%20to%20continue%20her%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20visited%20nearby%20doctors%20and%20PHCs%2C%20who%20ordered%20some%20basic%20tests%20and%20prescribed%20medicines.%20After%20two%20weeks%20of%20rest%20at%20home%2C%20the%2045-year-old%20did%20not%20experience%20any%20improvement.%20A%20doctor%20advised%20her%20to%20visit%20a%20hospital%20in%20Dehradun%20for%20better%20access%20to%20treatment%2C%20which%20involved%20travelling%20almost%20four%20hours%20to%20cover%20a%20distance%20of%20over%20150%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20Government-aided%20hospital%20in%20Dehradun%2C%20Chandrakala%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F140950%2Findian-scientists-develop-sensor-for-early-detection-of-chronic-kidney-disease%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echronic%20kidney%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20advised%20dialysis%20twice%20a%20week.%20As%20this%20treatment%20was%20not%20available%20near%20her%20residence%2C%20she%20had%20to%20travel%20to%20Dehradun%20and%20stay%20there%20for%20two%20nights%20every%20week%20to%20get%20the%20dialysis%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20single%20mother%2C%20being%20separated%20from%20her%20son%2C%20spending%20on%20travel%2C%20and%20eight%20nights%20at%20lodging%20every%20month%2C%20was%20much%20more%20than%20what%20she%20could%20afford%2C%20both%20physically%20and%20mentally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20faced%20by%20the%20ASHA%20worker%20resonates%20with%20many%20residing%20in%20rural%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%20According%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EGlobal%20Burden%20of%20Disease%20(GBD)%202015%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Chronic%20Kidney%20Disease%20(CKD)%20ranks%20as%20the%20eighth%20leading%20cause%20of%20death%20in%20India%2C%20largely%20because%20many%20patients%20develop%20complications%20leading%20to%20end-stage%20renal%20disease.%20A%20report%20published%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Lancet%3C%2Fem%3E%20estimated%20that%20two%20lakh%20people%20in%20India%20develop%20end-stage%20renal%20disease%20every%20year%20due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F250227%2Fshashank-moddhia-mumbai-startup-renal-project-affordable-kidney-dialysis-in-india-healthcare-him16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccess%20to%20long-term%20dialysis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20costs%20associated%20with%20dialysis%20care%20add%20to%20the%20financial%20woes%20of%20patients.%20Collaborating%20with%20the%20Uttarakhand%20Government%2C%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%20(THF)%20identified%20renal%20care%20as%20a%20major%20gap.%20Noticing%20that%20many%20residents%20in%20hilly%20areas%20were%20forced%20to%20migrate%20to%20Dehradun%20or%20Haldwani%20for%20dialysis%2C%20the%20organisation%20decided%20to%20bridge%20this%20gap%20by%20establishing%20last-mile%20availability%20of%20dialysis%20centres%20throughout%20the%20state%2C%20through%20the%20Hans%20Renal%20Care%20Centres%20initiative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarted%20with%20a%20single%20centre%20in%20March%202022%2C%20the%20programme%20has%20now%20expanded%20to%20include%20over%2027%20centres%20across%20Uttarakhand%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20Punjab.%20Over%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20THF%20has%20helped%20over%204%2C000%20patients%20access%20free%20dialysis%20through%20these%20centres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201188px)%20100vw%2C%201188px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FScreenshot-2024-03-14-093810_11zon-1710411627.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221188%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Hans%20Foundation%20has%20established%20last-mile%20availability%20of%20dialysis%20centres%20throughout%20the%20state%20through%20the%20Hans%20Renal%20Care%20Centres%20initiative.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FScreenshot-2024-03-14-093810_11zon-1710411627.jpg%201188w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FScreenshot-2024-03-14-093810_11zon-1710411627-300x156.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FScreenshot-2024-03-14-093810_11zon-1710411627-500x260.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FScreenshot-2024-03-14-093810_11zon-1710411627-768x400.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FScreenshot-2024-03-14-093810_11zon-1710411627-150x78.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-344875%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22618%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20Hans%20Foundation%20has%20established%20the%20last-mile%20availability%20of%20dialysis%20centres%20in%20rural%20areas%20through%20the%20Hans%20Renal%20Care%20Centres%20initiative.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EImproving%20access%20to%20dialysis%20in%20remote%20areas%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Government%20report%20has%20indicated%20an%20additional%20demand%20for%203.4%20crore%20dialysis%20procedures%20annually.%20However%2C%20the%20predominantly%20private%20dialysis%20centres%20cater%20to%20less%20than%20half%20of%20this%20demand%2C%20making%20them%20unaffordable%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F141684%2Fkamal-shahs-medical-problem-inspired-him-entrepreneur-nephroplus-dialysis%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epatients%20in%20need%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20the%20Government%20initiated%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20National%20Dialysis%20Program%20(PMNDP)%20in%202016%2C%20operating%20under%20a%20Public-Private%20Partnership%20(PPP)%20model%20to%20offer%20free%20dialysis%20services%20to%20economically%20disadvantaged%20individuals.%20This%20programme%20encompasses%20both%20hemodialysis%20and%20peritoneal%20dialysis%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hans%20Renal%20Care%20Centres%20collaborate%20with%20the%20Government%20to%20ensure%20free%20dialysis%20care%20in%20areas%20where%20this%20essential%20healthcare%20service%20isn%E2%80%99t%20available.%20Each%20centre%20is%20staffed%20with%20a%20medical%20officer%2C%20a%20technician%2C%20a%20nurse%2C%20and%20a%20housekeeping%20staff%2C%20and%20is%20equipped%20with%20three%20dialysis%20machines.%20In%20addition%2C%20a%20nephrologist%20is%20assigned%20to%20each%20centre%2C%20who%20makes%20monthly%20visits%20and%20is%20available%20for%20consultations%20and%20emergencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20renal%20care%20centres%20run%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%20Government%20and%20are%20located%20within%20the%20Government%20district%20and%20zonal%20hospitals.%20While%20the%20space%20is%20provided%20by%20the%20Government%2C%20THF%20provides%20the%20necessary%20staffing%2C%20machines%2C%20medicines%2C%20and%20furniture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20centres%20run%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%20Government%2C%20THF%20also%20operates%20a%20few%20private%20and%20independent%20Renal%20Care%20Centres%2C%20which%20provide%20cost-effective%20and%20subsidised%20dialysis%20care%20to%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20over%2064%2C000%20dialysis%20sessions%20have%20been%20conducted%20across%20the%2030%20centres%2C%20with%2028%20of%20them%20operating%20in%20partnership%20with%20different%20State%20Governments%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Uttarakhand%2C%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Meghalaya%20and%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20The%20remaining%20two%20are%20privately%20managed%20by%20the%20foundation.%20The%20private%20centres%2C%20present%20in%20Uttarakhand%20and%20Punjab%2C%20offer%20dialysis%20at%20subsidised%20rates.%20The%20foundation%20is%20also%20soon%20planning%20to%20expand%20to%20even%20more%20centres%20in%20collaboration%20with%20the%20State%20Governments%20of%20Jharkhand%20and%20Punjab%20in%20the%20coming%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FUntitled-design-3-1710411629.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chandrakala%2C%20an%20ASHA%20worker%2C%20who%20availed%20the%20benefit%20of%20The%20Hans%20Renal%20Centre%20in%20Karnaprayag.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FUntitled-design-3-1710411629.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FUntitled-design-3-1710411629-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2